			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Dark Souls: My (new) All-Time Favorite Game.
				</h2>
				

						
							
							
							
						
						
				<div class="content ">
					<div id="post_message_1833539">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							He is totally worth killing for his sweet loot, though.<br />
<br />
There are a couple of ways to fight him.  The one thing that applies to basically any non-cheese method is being able to time roll-dodges to evade his attacks effectively.  If you dodge too soon, he'll correct his swing and flatten you-- probably in the middle of a roll which is likely to kill you instantly.  If you dodge too late... well, you dodged too late.  But if you time it right, you'll have an opportunity to strike while he's lifting that Dragon Tooth off the ground.<br />
<br />
The standard tactic is to backstab him repeatedly.  To get a good backstab, run toward him when locked on and then hit the attack button right as you swing around.  Obviously, you'll need to time roll dodges pretty well to avoid his slams.  Alternately, with a good high-stability shield you can have some success just baiting out attacks that you are comfortable dodging and blocking everything else.  This takes a lot of patience or a pretty powerful weapon.<br />
<br />
He's very strong in all physical defense categories-- the strongest is slashing (katanas, scimitars, etc.) and the least strongest is striking (mace, club, etc.).  He is strong against magic, fire, and lightning and is extremely difficult to bleed.  Which basically leaves poison.  He can be poisoned.  A non-cheese method of poisoning would use rotten pine resin, poison daggers, and/or dung pies and then fighting him normally, with the DoT making the fight a little shorter than it would be otherwise.<br />
<br />
The cheese method is... once you get him poisoned, just run out of the tower and he'll de-aggro.  Make sure you aren't near any hollows (if you're approaching from the burg) or crystal golems (if you're coming from darkroot) then go catch up on the <a href="http://www.graffe.com/forums/showthread.php?63582-Hot-Chicks-Thread-With-Pics!-NSFW/page77" target="_blank">hot chicks thread with pics</a> while the poison finishes him off.<br />
<br />
Cheesing is harder than it sounds because, as you mentioned, there's no open space to hit him with the poison attacks.  You have to engage with him at least long enough to get him poisoned (and the throwing daggers/dung pies/etc. are a bit difficult to use mid-melee)
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="after_content">
				
