							Couple more things:  one important nugget of knowledge the game doesn't tell you explicitly is that rolling gives you a few frames of 100% invincibility.  You can, for example, roll directly *forward* through an oncoming fireball and if you time it right the fireball will go right through you.  <br />
<br />
Hopefully you got the Very Large Ember in the Depths.  Andre would love to have that and you would love for him to have it.  <br />
<br />
You can also go chat up Laurentius in Firelink if you rescued him, he sells some pretty good spells including <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=4UdcKGWmZMs" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Iron Flesh</a>.  (Iron Flesh was nerfed at some point after that video was made, apparently it was <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=O32ufmdQ6gk" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">ridiculously overpowered</a>, but it's still fun as it gives you a ton of poise and many enemy attacks will literally bounce off.)
						</blockquote>
