	</div>
</div>Not sure where he was? Unless absolutely necessary I've been avoiding spoilers. Half the fun in this game is discovering/figuring things out on your own.<br />
<br />
One question: I've ascended my weapons to +5 magic. Is divine above magic? I still can't seem to hit ghosts.<br />
<br />
Just from an observational standpoint this game seems like one big puzzle requiring you to go get this and that to defeat this or that comfortably. Or you can take things on the hard way which usually results in a corpse run. Probing suicide missions do have their place. It also has a bit of a tennis feel where you push harder before you die, then must be very cautious on your corpse run. Also with the way the architecture wraps on itself it feels a lot like a rubics cube; pretty original, ingenious design. I wish more games would venture out from the blueprints of success like it. Coolest thing about this game for both of us I think is they just released 2 and it's highly rated too. Just a little anticipation backdrop. I assume you venture out into the wider world (no spoilers please!). Will need a comp upgrade first, though.<br />
<br />
Thanks again for recommending this. I second that. Even for those who don't like melee, it grows on you.
						</blockquote>
