			<div class="postrow has_after_content">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Dark Souls: My (new) All-Time Favorite Game.
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1833565">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							LOL oops.  Andre is easily the most useful NPC in the game.  Do NOT kill any more blacksmiths!  Did you at least buy the weapon smithbox before killing him?<br />
<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				he seemed to just snatch it for his own
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>This actually gave him the ability to upgrade your weapons to divine, in the same way that Rickert upgrades your weapons to magic.  That said, you can still make it through the game without him and get plenty of powerful weapons, you'll just be limited to magic and fire upgrade paths, or &quot;unique&quot; items that use twinkling titanite, like the Black Knight Sword.<br />
<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				One question: I've ascended my weapons to +5 magic. Is divine above magic? I still can't seem to hit ghosts.
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Magic and Divine are basically equivalent, except that Divine weapons scale with faith and Magic weapons scale with Intelligence.  Also, divine weapons get bonus damage against dark creatures.  To upgrade magic weapons past Magic +5, you'll need the &quot;Large Magic Ember&quot; or the &quot;Enchanted Ember.&quot;  If you find one of those embers, Rickert will take it (don't kill him lol), and then when you 'Modify Equiment' you'll see that you'll be able to upgrade it to either Magic+6 or Enchanted (+0).  Then you'll be able to upgrade to Magic +10 or Enchanted +5, which are both terminal upgrades.<br />
<br />
Ghosts can be damaged with cursed weapons, though you won't have any of those for awhile (the most common cursed weapon actually drops from the ghosts themselves... the other ones you won't be able to get since you killed andre :P) and even then, ghost's attacks will still ignore all your armor.<br />
<br />
The main way to fight ghosts is to be cursed yourself.  When you are cursed it doesn't matter what weapon you use, and your armor will actually work.  There are two ways to gain a cursed status, I'll leave you to discover those on your own.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="after_content">
				
