				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Dark Souls: My (new) All-Time Favorite Game.
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1833592">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							Heh, yeah I never killed that guy but MANY players do.  My first playthrough, I accidentally aggroed Griggs.  I tried to quit and reload but that didn't help, so I just killed him, he drops a sweet ring that lets you sneak up on enemies from behind.  But you can get that ring eventually anyway and Griggs sells a ton of useful magic.  One important thing to realize is that if you accidentally aggro an NPC, you can clear the aggro by going to Oswald up in the Church where you rang the first bell.  You pay him an indulgence (based on your current Soul Level), he forgives your sin and aggro is reset.<br />
<br />
Seriously, you can totally make it through the game without Andre if you want to, but you'll almost certainly want to play again eventually without killing him to check out some Boss Soul weapons.  Boss Soul weapons aren't super-amazing or anything, but they do tend to have some fun qualities.  For example there's an axe with a shockwave attack and a katana that does extra damage when you have more humanity (but also harms you each hit).  There's also a spear that shoots lightning, but you can actually get that one without Andre since you can find a lightning spear that can be used for the upgrade.<br />
<br />
Just curious what does your current stat allocation look like?  Honestly, the fact that you got the Black Knight Sword means that you don't really have to worry about weapons at all if you don't want to.  More weapons like that are available as you progress, too, for any stat build.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
