			<div class="postrow">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Dark Souls: My (new) All-Time Favorite Game.
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1833593">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				There was no indication his menu had changed.
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Yeah this can be a little confusing.<br />
<br />
The key is the &quot;Modify Equipment&quot; line.  Rickert has that one, too.  At the start, when you try to modify equipment it'll tell you either &quot;Need ember to ascend weapons&quot; or &quot;no weapons for ascension&quot;:<br />
<br />
You need to give an ember to the blacksmith to unlock ascension capability, and to actually have a weapon show up there to be eligible for ascension it needs to be maxed out in its current category.  For example when you upgraded your weapon to +5 normal, it became eligible for ascension to magic by Rickert (who doesn't need an ember to do the magic upgrade).  Before you upgraded it to +5 it would have told you &quot;no weapons for ascension.&quot;<br />
<br />
After giving Andre the Divine Ember, if you'd looked in the Modify Equipment submenu, you'd have noticed a new selection at the top that looked like a white orb, and any +5 weapons would be there eligible for ascension to divine.
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<div class="cleardiv"></div>
		</div>
	</div>
