		<div class="postbody">
			<div class="postrow">
				
				
				<h2 class="title icon icon0">
					Re: Dark Souls: My (new) All-Time Favorite Game.
				</h2>
				

						
						
				<div class="content">
					<div id="post_message_1833682">
						<blockquote class="postcontent restore ">
							<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				So you can convert any weapon to divine if the smith has an ember?
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>Well, there's only one divine ember in the game, and Andre is the only blacksmith who can make divine weapons.<br />
<br />
<div class="bbcode_container">
	<div class="bbcode_quote">
		<div class="quote_container">
			<div class="bbcode_quote_container"></div>
			
				I've invested too much time to hit restart because of one mistake.
			
		</div>
	</div>
</div>One thing to point out:  A certain amount of time investment carries over to a second playthrough.  While drops have to be gotten again, you don't have to spend as much time learning how to do stuff, where everything is, and what the enemy attack patterns are.  You can, for example, take the Master Key and run and grab Astora's Straight Sword before you even go to undead burg.<br />
<br />
Speaking of Astora's, it's great in the first half of the game and great against undead skeletons in particular.  But later in the game though, it will likely be outclassed by other weapons due to the low base damage and 3-way split on scaling (you need to level strength, dex, AND faith to get the most out of it).  Astora's moveset is actually identical to the regular Longsword moveset, so you'd probably like the regular longsword, too.  The broadsword is comparatively shorter and doesn't have that nice thrusting R2.  I definitely recommend raising your strength to 20 so you can try out the Black Knight Sword, though.  It's slower than Astora's, but can ultimately be far more damaging and is great for many bosses.<br />
<br />
One general tip:  Consider raising your Endurance.  It's the like king of stats.  Endurance raises your stamina (the green bar in combat) which is used for everything except spells and items.  Endurance also raises your equip load, which raises your rolling threshold.  For example, if you had a 40 endurance, you'd be mid-rolling with your current equipment (currently you are fat-rolling.  Notice that screen quake every time you roll?). <br />
<br />
For specific options you can take, given that you won't have access to divine weapons without Andre:<br />
<br />
<ul><li style="">Keep leveling strength and use black knight weapons.  There are 4 different variants and all of them are cool.<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px">
<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>Spoiler</b> for <i>other strength weapons</i>: <input type="button" value="Show" style="width:45px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != 'inline') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'inline'; this.value = 'Hide'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none';  this.value = 'Show'; }">
</div>
<div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;">
<div style="display: none;">
There's also the <a href="http://darksouls.wikidot.com/giant-s-halberd" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Giant's Halberd</a>, <a href="http://darksouls.wikidot.com/gravelord-sword" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Gravelord Sword</a>, and the <a href="http://darksouls.wikidot.com/dragon-tooth" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Dragon Tooth</a>. 
</div>
</div>
</div></li><li style="">Stop leveling strength and dex, focus on endurance and vitality, and use mostly fire or chaos weapons (and switch to Astora's or whatever when you hit a fire-resistant enemy).  Fire and Chaos weapons have no scaling and ignore stats completely, assuming you have the stats to wield the base weapon.  I'd recommend trying out a Fire Battle Axe or Fire Longsword first.  The weapons dropped by ghosts also have almost no scaling.<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px">
<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>Spoiler</b> for <i>Fire/Chaos weapons</i>: <input type="button" value="Show" style="width:45px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != 'inline') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'inline'; this.value = 'Hide'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none';  this.value = 'Show'; }">
</div>
<div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;">
<div style="display: none;">
There is a secret blacksmith in the Catacombs that can upgrade your normal +5 weapons to fire weapons.  There are two embers you can find and give him to enable either +10 Fire or +5 Chaos weapons from there 
</div>
</div>
</div></li><li style="">Level dex and use:<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px">
<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>Spoiler</b> for <i>Unique Dex Weapons</i>: <input type="button" value="Show" style="width:45px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != 'inline') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'inline'; this.value = 'Hide'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none';  this.value = 'Show'; }">
</div>
<div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;">
<div style="display: none;">
Silver Knight Straight Sword and Silver Knight Spear.  Both are great weapons.  The Silver Knight Straight Sword is notably buffable 
</div>
</div>
</div></li><li style="">It's not too late to go the intelligence route; though if you do, I would stop leveling faith at 20 or so, unless you find some miracle you really want to use that requires something higher.  Then, when your int gets high enough, you can use Velka's Talisman (buy from Oswald), which lets you cast miracles using your INT stat.  Maybe play a corrupted paladin who turns to magic after losing his faith.  You could level your int up to 40 and have access to lots of sorcery spells and any magic/enchanted weapon you want</li><li style="">There are three more faith-oriented weapons that you can get without Andre.  Warning... definitely spoilers in this next section:<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px">
<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px"><b>Spoiler</b> for <i>MAJOR SPOILERS</i>: <input type="button" value="Show" style="width:45px;font-size:10px;margin:0px;padding:0px;" onClick="if (this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display != 'inline') { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'inline'; this.value = 'Hide'; } else { this.parentNode.parentNode.getElementsByTagName('div')[1].getElementsByTagName('div')[0].style.display = 'none';  this.value = 'Show'; }">
</div>
<div class="alt2" style="margin: 0px; padding: 6px; border: 1px inset;">
<div style="display: none;">
The Crescent Axe, which basically works just like Astora's Straight sword except it's a weirdly long axe instead of a sword.  Not a very popular weapon.<br />
<br />
<a href="http://darksouls.wikidot.com/grant" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">Grant</a>, a huge club requiring 50 strength and 30 faith to wield.  Dropped by Paladin Leeroy (yep, WoW reference) when you defeat his phantom in the Tomb of the Giants.  Note you must be human for him to invade, and Tomb of the Giants is an end-game area.<br />
<br />
<a href="http://darksouls.wikidot.com/dragonslayer-spear" target="_blank" rel="nofollow">The Dragonslayer Spear</a>, Ornstein's weapon.  While this requires 24 strength and 24 dex to wield, it's damage output will be mediocre until Dex, Strength, and Faith are all raised.  It also requires defeating Ornstein last.  It does have much more stamina/poise drain than typical spears, though, and attacks fast, so it's a pretty good weapon overall.  Oh yeah, it shoots lightning.  To get this without using Andre requires obtaining the Lightning Spear from Sen's fortress, downgrading it to +10 then using it with Ornstein's soul at the Giant Blacksmith.<br />
 
</div>
</div>
</div></li></ul><br />
<br />
Helpful chart:<br />
<br />
Without Andre, you are basically limited to the items on the bottom half of the page.<br />
<br />
<img src="http://darksouls.wikidot.com/local--files/upgrade/upgrade-chart.jpg" border="0" alt="" />
						</blockquote>
					</div>

					
				</div>
			</div>
			
